            <summary>
              <p> </p>
              <p>In addition to the image in the catalogue Déroche, <ref target="https://www.zotero.org/groups/corpuscoranicum_pub/items/itemKey/QJQEKNSJ">The Abbasid Tradition, London 1992</ref>, p. 140 (fol. 2r), this catalogue shows also images of pages fol. 1r, fol. 1v, and fol. 2v. </p>
              <p>Cf. catalogue entry by François Déroche about fragment KFQ 40 (Déroche, <ref target="https://www.zotero.org/groups/corpuscoranicum_pub/items/itemKey/QJQEKNSJ" sameAs="QJQEKNSJ" type="zotero">The Abbasid Tradition, London 1992</ref>, p. 140): "76 / Two folios / 10th century AD / Fragmentary; largest dimensions now 12.1 x 17.7 cm (folio I) and 12.4 x 18 cm (folio 2); there are 7 lines to the page / <hi rend="italic">Material</hi> Parchment; the recto is the hair side / <hi rend="italic">Text area</hi> 6.8 x 12.5 cm / <hi rend="italic">Script</hi> Style NS.III / <hi rend="italic">Accession no</hi>. KFQ 40 / The text - <hi rend="italic">Sūrat Hūd</hi> (XI), verses 31-36 and 45-49 - is written in brown to dark brown ink. A few diacritical marks have been added, and red dots are used to indicate the vocalization; the green dots appear to be corrections. The verses are not divided. A gold Kufic <hi rend="italic">hāʾ</hi> marks the end of a group of five verses. The lower right-hand corner of folio I has been lost." </p>
            </summary>
